{
  "texts": [
    "The upper part of Figure 7b shows the percent deviation of equilibrium contact angles derived from the Young-Dupré equation compared to those calculated directly.",
    "The two methods",
    "agree well, with a discrepancy of 10-15% for some points.",
    "Importantly, this agreement provides a direct validation of the phantom-wall thermodynamic-integration method for the present system, as the work-of-adhesion values obtained from the phantom-wall protocol reproduce independently measured equilibrium contact angles via the Young-Dupré relation.",
    "The wetting angle decreases non-linearly with increase in hydroxyl portion."
  ]
}